    "We added 10% systematic uncertainty to the real data in the evaluation process for DIFMAP because the image generation process did not use closure quantities (unlike the RML methods), and down-weighted the ALMA visibilites during self-calibration, resulting in comparable normalized χ 2 values to the RML methods.",
    "For the Bayesian imaging methods, the fit quality is assessed through comparisons of the complex visibility reduced χ 2 for THEMIS, the visibility amplitude and closure phase reduced χ 2 for Comrade, log-likelihoods, the logarithm of the Bayesian evidence (log(Z)), and distribution of the residuals.",
